The paper discusses the use of procedural content generation (PCG) in videogames and other games to generate content algorithmically, and how this can be used to increase the generality of machine learning methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of PCG in generating levels and characters, which could fall under the Graphics (cs.GR) category. The paper also mentions the use of PCG in optimizing and solving constraints, which could fall under the Computation and Language (cs.CL) category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of PCG in benchmarking new machine learning algorithms, which could fall under the Game Theory (cs.GT) category.
